So maybe i don't have the stress tolerance other people have. like i care about people who have to work after school on weekdays and work weekends just to pay for school or necessities like that....but....like i don't really care if they are able to handle it and i can't. i don't compare myself to them and say "wow, they have it so much harder than me...maybe i'm not so stressed out." i FEEL stressed out and i don't care if other people can deal with more than what i'm dealing with. 


"i thought i would have a golden age. now it's miserable. raising up ungrateful people...hang out with who?! all christmas i didn't see you hanging out with anyone...or summer. always so lazy, don't wash your face, don't take a shower and just go through a day. Those with high grades don't spend a day doing nothing. they're always on the go. Have you paid? you didn't have to pay yet....pull her out. i don't want to deal with her. wasted $900. .......................................................................

I believe -
. . . that just because two people argue, it doesn't mean they don't love each other. And just because they don't argue, it doesn't mean they do.

I believe -
. . . that we don't have to change friends if we understand that
friends change. Remember that!

I believe -
. . ..that no matter how good a friend is, they're going to hurt you every once in a while and you must forgive them for that. Even if you think you can't.

I believe -
. . . that true friendship continues to grow, even over the longest distance. Same goes for true love.

I believe -
. . . that you can do something in an instant that will give you
heartache for life.

I believe -
. . . that it's taking me a long time to become the person I want to be.

I believe -
. . . that you should always leave loved ones with loving words. It may be the last time you see/talk them.

I believe -
. . . that you can keep going long after you think you can't.

I believe -
. . . that we are responsible for what we do, no matter how we feel.

I believe -
. . . that either you control your attitude or it controls you.

I believe -
. . .that heroes are the people who do what has to be done when it needs to be done, regardless of the consequences.

I believe -
. . . that money is a lousy way of keeping score.

I believe -
. . . that my best friend and I can do anything or nothing and have the best time.

I believe -
. . . that sometimes the people you expect to kick you when you're down, will be the ones to help you get back up.

I believe -
. . . that sometimes when I'm angry I have the right to be angry, but that doesn't give me the right to be cruel.

I believe -
. . . that maturity has more to do with what types of experiences you've had and what you've learned from them and less to do with how many birthdays you've celebrated.

I believe -
. . . that it isn't always enough to be forgiven by others. Sometimes you have to learn to forgive yourself.

I believe -
. . . that no matter how bad your heart is broken the world doesn't stop for your grief.

I believe -
. .. . that our background and circumstances may have influenced who we are, but we are responsible for who we become.

I believe -
. . . that you shouldn't be so eager to find out a secret. It could
change your life forever.

I believe -
. . . two people can look at the exact same thing and see something totally different.

I believe -
. . . that your life can be changed in a matter of hours by people who don't even know you or by people that you don't even know.

I believe -
. . . that even when you think you have no more to give, when a friend cries out to you - you will find the strength to help.

I believe -
. . . that credentials on the wall do not make you a decent human being.

I believe -
. . . that the people you care about most in life are taken from you too soon. (We must keep praying for the ones we love!)

So this weekend was supposed to be awesome because it was our youth fall retreat and it was going to be amazing since we were cooking ourselves, getting to know each other more, having bible devotions with the girls. 
I come home and i'm happy but tired...glad to be home but not in the mood to talk; i had about 4-5 hours of sleep every day. I talk to my dad in the car about how it went though i know i didn't really say much because i was tired and didn't want to talk. i guess it's my bad habit of when i'm tired, i get grouchy and don't want to say anything. My mom asks how it went and gets the usual response of "Good" so she asks more questions. i TELL her that i'm not in the mood to talk but i'll tell her later so she gets kinda grouchy and tells me to unpack and shower. At dinner, she starts asking again how it went and what we talked about; i said that some stuff were more private because it was a serious talk and really, she doesn't need to know, lest she uses it to guess who said what and use it against them. She does that but [angrily&violently] denies it. Then she starts saying stuff like "it's prolly those 'sissy' stuff...nothing spiritual, about God...etc" so i start getting pissed cuz she doesn't know what she's saying and it just making stuff up; to get me angry? i don't know. She makes random assumptions and when i say that they're not true she yells "DID I EVER SAY THAT? YOU ALWAYS TAKE THINGS TO NEGATIVELY! DON'T PUT WORDS IN MY MOUTH..blah blah" But the thing is she DID say those things and it confuses me all the time when she says that she didn't say it and i start thinking that i just made it up. i know she said those things but when i say that she's being negative and i don't agree with her, she blows up and starts bursting all these nonsensical things and makes things 100x worse. She assumes the worst of people usually and judges them by one incident. The thing with J was that she was coming to our retreat but doesn't go to our church. my mom starts saying all this bad stuff about her and how she's only there for fun and to hang out; not serious at all. Of course, my mom doesn't know her and already judges the reasons for her actions. Yes, she probably went to hang out but she's also really serious about God and when sharing came, it really showed that she was struggling with something. Of course, my mom doesn't care and thinks everything girls talk about in a serious sharing is "sissy". And she asks why i don't talk to her.


I want to tell my mom things. I wanted to tell her about Ryan a couple of times but the time was never right and i didn't know how to bring it up. I wanted to ask for her advice but i'm scared to incase she starts rebuking me, telling me that i'm wrong, that i shouldn't think of such things, and bans me from seeing him. I wanted to tell her how nice he is and how he's worried about me...saying i should sleep more because i look tired; that i should wash my face so i don't fall asleep when i'm studying; saying he misses me; that he's waiting outside my math class for me even though there's half an hour left of class. But i can't tell her those things. i don't want her to judge him and therefore making me see him differently; i like the way i see him now and i don't want my perspective to change. I know she cares for me even at times when she says she hates me and wishes i wasn't her daughter. The little and the big things she does out of her way for me really shows her love. i just can't talk to her no matter how much i want to.

i don't know why i keep my old entries where i was immature and embarassed myself without knowing it. How stupid i once was to, without knowing anything, debate on important topics that affected how other saw Christians. 

I'm reading a book. The End of Religion. It talks about how Jesus didn't come to Earth to start another religion, but rather to abolish all religions, the rules, and the laws that 'bind' us. He was very controversial and he always created scandals because his teachings were so 'out there' and didn't follow the old laws. i find that really interesting. It's like Josh says...Jesus would be kicked out of modern churches because of the words he speaks which sound like blasphemy because we are so tied up in the law. But...many others are considered blasphemous; 'false prophets'. Back in Jesus' time, the Pharasees thought the words that Jesus was saying was "blasphemous"...if he was here today, would i say his words are blasphemous? would i be able to tell between him and false prophets? i don't think so. If a book is popular in a Christian store, the thoughts and ideas become the Christian reader. Yes, they do question..but because it was in a Christian bookstore and so many people bought the book, it's considered true. The End of Religion. What's written in there sounds accurate and so empowering as it gives Christians and non-Christians a different view of when Jesus came down and what he was trying to do. But how do i know if it's truely accurate? Bible passages are used, the logic makes sense and it gives a new meaning in being 'spiritual' and not 'religious'. i think false prophets sound accurate to their listeners; or else they're not very good at their job. If people were to believe in them...if I were to believe them...yes, it would be my fault...but can i not go to Heaven if it leads me astray? God looks at the heart, not as other people see others, so i suppose as long as my heart's looking for Him..?

I got baptized today. i said my testimony, i got dunked, i came back out. There were so many people there congratulating me and wishing me the best. so many of my friends were there too. But the only person who really mattered...was you. you surprised me and came to watch...but you were with a girl. And it got me thinking. She might not be your girlfriend; she could be your cousin. But that's not the point. When i saw you with another girl, it reminded me that you're in a relationship with someone else. i don't want to come inbetween or break you guys up; i'm not capable of being in her place. But i can't stand on the side seeing you with your girlfriend; be super happy when you talk to me and really sad when you're not there. I hate the ups and downs that come with you. So i want to give you up. i can't actually cuz you were never mine...but in my heart i guess to give you up is to let go and move on. i can't see my future with you. you're not the guy for me. i don't want to be the third wheel. i can't be just friends with you. so with all those negative thoughts, the only think i can do is forget about you and hope you don't come back. i'm too young to be thinking that i'm in love, though not about being in love. we're not 'meant to be' however cliched it might sound...we're not. So i want to forget about you and hope you're happy with your girlfriend and hope i can continue my life without you. 


i need to return a book to you...i'll just give it to a friend.

N =\= R

What am i supposed to think when you say "I miss you" and i miss you too. I can't like you. You're off-limits. You have a girlfriend, you're in university, you're 6 years older than me, and you're not the guy for me. Sometimes i get confused and I wonder if you're just playing me and leading me on; fooling around and flirting. But when i hear your voice on the phone and when i see you, all my doubts go away and i smile and get extremely nervous. I don't really like that feeling. The tripping-over-words, making-no-sense, wracking-my-brain-to-think-of-what-to-say kind of talking from me. I never know what to say to you and you don't have much to say either. Another reason why i don't think we're good for each other. Whenever i'm with you or talking on the phone with you, my mind becomes blank and the things i wanted to tell you sound stupid and insignificant. I don't understand how i can have so much fun teasing and joking with my guy friends but when it comes to guys i like, i can't. I actually can't loosten myself around you and just have fun and be stupid. i guess i care too much about what you think that i'm not letting me be myself. That's not a good thing, is it.... i wish that i could see you more. But when i think about if that happened and i did see you more, we would always be awkward and there would just be silences when neither of us know what to do. I always hear from my friends how they talk for hours with their boyfriends everyday...and i wonder what they could be talking about that there's always something to say. I really want to ask you who i am to you, how you really feel about me, why you like me, and about us in general, i guess. But i can't gather my courage to ask you. Who am i to ask you anyways. i could just be a friend and for someone you treat a friend to suddenly ask you about your relationship and if you like them is kind of weird. I don't know how you feel about me. This could be completely one-sided, in which case i would sound stupid and love-sick, which i probably am.

So I am procrastinating again. Shocking. I have got to stop this habit of mine, but it is like an addiction - its claws have grabbed a hold of me and every step away feels like my skin is being wretched from me. But the longer I stay still, the greater the grasp it has. Either I stay and let it devour me...or I try to break away, and in doing so, become...torn. I think I might go crazy.

I am mainly writing here because I am hoping it will help me focus - on something, on anything. I have also taken up not using contractions, as in my essay, I will not be able to do so. Good practice, I guess. They are a big habit. Now I sound funny. Wonderful.

My mind is a mess...Sounds like the beginning of a poem. Perhaps I should write a poem, starting with, "My mind is a mess..." Perhaps it might actually be good. Hmm. I am a crappy poet though. Better let someone else come up with that idea who can actually write poems. =(

                                            Puzzling feelings. 
                                                                                                                   Swirling thoughts. 
             Jumbled memories. 
                                                                      My brain might rot.

Haha! Random poem [almost].

So I have come to the point in which I must empty my brain, lest I explode. Which would be extremely messy considering my brain is mush.

I guess I'm tired of waiting. Tired of thinking, wondering, dreaming, being confused. So I have come up with a plan and though I am almost positive that it is not going to work, I shall persist. I have decided to not think about it anymore. It is a simple plan, really. An obvious one. But it will definitely not be easy. I hate plans like this. You think it is easy. It sounds easy. But it is NOT. Like my English essay. One might think it is easy [though even in the beginning, I knew it was going to be a killer assignment. In the worst way possible]. It sounds easy enough, especially if the teacher has basically outlined the essay for the class and all the students have to do is write, find quotes, and support them [but I knew]. The teacher had also given extra time to work on this essay, which consists of two extra class periods, a weekend, and taking it home overnight. Yet still, my paper refuses to be filled with writing - the 1000 words that are needed are still lacking. But I shall desist.

"My life is like a garden and I am only simply walking through it - missing all the flowers that decorate my way"
                        -Natty, in her time of lethargicness and thoughtful thinking

I really like him. I do. And yes, I know that my plan was not to think about it anymore, but it is hard, especially since I am missing him now. Tomorrow has become that much more grim - I shall not see him tomorrow. This...feeling. I like him. But I hate the feelings that he brings me.

-sigh- Feeling pretty dead. Not good. Especially since i have 3 labs to finish. Man, i hate science =.=

my [little] problem:
My best friend...i love her so much & she's always there for me
My crush...he's the randomest person ever & every time i see him, i can't help but smile
One event...changed...a lot

I can't help but think what would have happened if they never met. Me & him would still be in that "i-know-you-like-me-and-vice-versa" friendship [?] Haha. Maybe I should have done something earlier? Asked him out? But i'm not that kind of girl. Me & her would still have a super close friendship with nothing and nobody inbetween. 
Now, i feel bad because lately i've been kind of un-responsive whenever she talks to me. It's not her fault. She doesn't know. Course, i've told her before. The me-liking-him thing. But maybe she forgot. They look so good together. She's like...a girl version of him. So much so that it's actually kinda weird haha. They're crazy, outgoing, random, and never run out of things to say. They're both the two ppl, aside from my family & other best friends, that i [love] most in the world. 
So i asked him. Whether he liked her or not. But he's the shy type of guy. As if he would tell me, right? No. He wouldn't. 
His best friend talked to me the other day. Was asking how it went and how our 'relationship' was going [do we even have one? in the sense that he's mentioning?] Said a bunch of things which just made me feel...sad. Because all of this was before and things have changed. Asking me to the prom? Not happening [don't know how i would reply]. Saying that he liked me was a fact. 

Maybe i should stop. I don't want to keep feeling this way. I hate love games.
Me? i'm going to be a rock for the next few days. That, or i'm going to live under one.

i miss it a lot. We had fun. Goofed off. Pretty good friend. On MSN anyways. But who can trust that? i know now that i can't. 
Friendships come and go. But yours i miss the most. You brought out a different side of me. a funner side, i suppose. Me, the uninteresting girl always caught with a book. You loosened me. And then let me go. I can't wind myself up again. Worse, i can't live being loose without you with me. But you refuse to, so i must cope with living like this. Have you not noticed me, from the corner of your eye? Has the pitiful girl sitting in a crowd by herself not caught your attention? Will these feelings that i torment myself with everyday that i see you, never go away? i don't want to live like this. nor do i want you back. i'm afraid. though it was short, i thought perhaps you were the one who could unravel me. Not leave me half-naked, standing on your driveway in the winter. It was winter. Christmas. Man, i miss that year. i miss everything that happened. And i miss you.

When The Music Fades

When the music fades, all is stripped away, and i simply come. Longing just to bring something that's of worth, that will bless Your heart.

I'll bring You more that a song, for a song in itself, is not what You have required. You search much deeper within, through the way things appear, You're looking into my heart.

I'm coming back to the heart of worship, and it's all about You, it's all about You, Jesus. I'm sorry Lord for the thing i've made it, and it's all about You, it's all about You, Jesus.

King of endless worth, noone could express, how much You deserve. Though I'm weak and poor, all i have is Yours, every single breath.

I'll bring You more that a song, for a song in itself, is not what You have required. You search much deeper within, through the way things appear, You're looking into my heart.

I'm coming back to the heart of worship, and it's all about You, it's all about You, Jesus. I'm sorry Lord for the thing i've made it, and it's all about You, it's all about You, Jesus.
